<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8" standalone="no"?><?Xpress productLine="ncc-clause" ?><clause id="_c80d9ee9-06e7-48b5-a3dd-d4e12cf60543" outputclass="ncc-clause"><meta><facet building="Class 1a"/><facet building="Class 1b"/><facet building="Class 2"/><facet building="Class 4"/><facet building="Class 5"/><facet building="Class 6"/><facet building="Class 7a"/><facet building="Class 7b"/><facet building="Class 8"/><facet building="Class 9b"/><facet building="Class 10a"/><facet building="Class 10b"/><facet building="Class 10c"/></meta><sptc>S17C12</sptc><title id="_102f7312-d5f8-4b2b-a41e-fb5b683f8ded">Residential care buildings</title><archive-num>2019: Spec E1.5: 12</archive-num><subclause id="_3b955fff-cd36-41e1-bcc6-9aac61e2b50c" outputclass="subclause"><title id="_31150a14-906c-4928-9c31-189f74ee4272">SubClause</title><num>1</num><p>In addition to the provisions of AS 2118.4, a sprinkler system in—</p><ol outputclass="alpha"><li id="_41f018bb-f76b-423e-a461-ebb0b7e6482b">a Class 3 building used as a <xref format="dita" href="/tmp/QppServer/Publishing/5e2c1f63-e589-4ce1-95e8-5c3e286a7aff/1436_4.0.0.xml#_b286ccd1-342e-49e1-95e9-4b6a0a6c0447" id="_9e2e08cb-4681-48e6-b4ad-ba803b72d81e" scope="local" type="abcb-glossentry">residential care building</xref>; or</li><li id="_f75172a5-105e-4635-9c71-d21e347d354f">a Class 9a <xref format="dita" href="/tmp/QppServer/Publishing/5e2c1f63-e589-4ce1-95e8-5c3e286a7aff/1333_0.4.0.xml#_1f5fbee8-584a-4244-9286-ebf9d8ebb04a" id="_709c9bae-3385-420c-bf3f-4fdd36f611b9" scope="local" type="abcb-glossentry">health-care building</xref> used as a <xref format="dita" href="/tmp/QppServer/Publishing/5e2c1f63-e589-4ce1-95e8-5c3e286a7aff/1436_4.0.0.xml#_b286ccd1-342e-49e1-95e9-4b6a0a6c0447" id="_6873062b-eb06-4f7f-9902-7fa7d03b8079" scope="local" type="abcb-glossentry">residential care building</xref>; or</li><li id="_bfdd2fc6-7465-4942-8d69-50a09befc50c">a Class 9c building,</li></ol><p>must comply with sub-clause (2).</p></subclause><subclause id="_e0c47eb7-ecd5-4800-9fbe-0413f0138054" outputclass="subclause"><title id="_a4bf7ff9-f64e-4a8a-90c9-4ffe12390cc1">SubClause</title><num>2</num><p>Any sprinkler system referred to in (1) must—</p><ol outputclass="alpha"><li id="_8b3ed7c7-bf55-421d-ba23-a7be53a825b2">be provided with a monitored main stop valve in accordance with AS 2118.1; and</li><li id="_258ee315-f53d-4c1c-a72f-472ee8af185e">be permanently connected with a direct data link or other approved monitoring system to a fire station or fire station dispatch centre.</li></ol></subclause></clause>